<testgrp id="RM000001BFY008X_07_0011" proc-id="RM0250U___00007JW00000">
<testtitle>CHECK WHETHER DTC OUTPUT RECURS (DTC P050A AND/OR P050B)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<ptxt>In this operation, the engine must be cold (the same level as the engine coolant temperature recorded in the freeze frame data).</ptxt>
</atten3>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to the ON position.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Clear the DTCs (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000PDK01MX"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Switch the ECM from normal mode to check mode using the tester (See page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000000PDL01QX"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Start the engine to idle for a minute.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Stable fast idling.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Read the DTCs.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
